# Serah Local Assistant

Local-first AI assistant project with memory, planning, research workflows, and safety gates.

## Overview

Serah is a local-first personal AI assistant project built to help with planning, research, memory, accountability, and controlled AI workflows.

## Purpose

The goal of Serah is to create a practical AI command system that can help organize projects, summarize information, create research briefs, maintain memory through an Obsidian vault, and support daily execution without relying fully on cloud tools.

## Current Features

* Local-first assistant concept
* Obsidian-based memory system
* Research brief workflow
* Daily planning and accountability loop
* Claude/ChatGPT-assisted development workflow
* Ask-me-first safety gates for sensitive actions
* Project handoff documents and structured task tickets

## Tools and Technologies

* Python
* Obsidian
* Ollama/local AI models
* Claude / Claude Code
* ChatGPT
* GitHub
* Windows development environment

## Safety Design

Serah is designed with safety limits. Sensitive actions such as spending money, deleting files, installing major software, exposing services, connecting accounts, or handling private information require human approval first.

## Status

This project is in active development. The current focus is improving the assistant workflow, documenting progress, and building a clean public portfolio version.

